						               													<description>Justice is a new game system in which the players will participate in a trial, one of you will be the defense attorney, the prosecutor will be in charge of bringing the accusation and the rest will form the court.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each case proposes a unique enigma, but with multiple resolutions that each game will lead to a completely different trial.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After long days of illness, on January 21, 1907, the 36-year-old journalist and writer Bertram Fletcher Robinson is found dead at his home in London. Although the symptoms fit with typhoid fever and peritonitis, there are indications that the victim may have been poisoned. Scotland Yard narrows the investigation down to three suspicious people, although only one of them is finally brought to trial a few months later...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher (translated)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Justice es un nuevo sistema de juego en el que los jugadores participar&amp;eacute;is en un juicio, uno de vosotros ser&amp;aacute; el abogado defensor, el fiscal se encargar&amp;aacute; de llevar la acusaci&amp;oacute;n y el resto formar&amp;aacute; el tribunal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cada caso propone un &amp;uacute;nico enigma, pero con m&amp;uacute;ltiples resoluciones que cada partida llevar&amp;aacute;n a un juicio completamente distinto.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Tras largos d&amp;iacute;as de enfermedad, el 21 de enero de 1907 aparece muerto en su domicilio en Londres el periodista y escritor Bertram Fletcher Robinson, de 36 a&amp;ntilde;os de edad. Aunque los s&amp;iacute;ntomas encajan con unas fiebres tifoideas y una peritonitis, se hallan indicios de que la v&amp;iacute;ctima pudo haber sido envenenada. Scotland Yard reduce la investigaci&amp;oacute;n a tres personas sospechosas, aunque finalmente s&amp;oacute;lo una de ellas es llevada a juicio unos meses despu&amp;eacute;s&amp;hellip;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
